Excluding three patients with confirmed MERS-CoV infection who were not identified in the initial patient contact investigation (appendix p 5), the overall attack rate for patients in the emergency room was 4% (30 of 675). Patients in group A had the highest attack rate (20% [23 of 117]), compared with 5% (three of 58) in group B and 1% (four of 500) in group C (figure 3
). After adjusting for age, sex, underlying disease, and groups, patients in group A had the highest risk for MERS-CoV infection (table 2
). In group B, all three patients who had MERS-CoV infection had time overlap in the radiology suite with Patient 14.
